-- Lanxess to Hire About 10% More Staff in 2012, Sueddeutsche Says
-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 2012-01-27T07:17:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-27/lanxess-to-hire-about-10-more-staff-in-2012-sueddeutsche-says.html
Lanxess AG (LXS)  Chief Executive Officer
Axel Heitmann said the company will hire about 10 percent more
workers this year,  Sueddeutsche Zeitung  reported, citing an
interview with the manager.  Heitmann is confident about 2012 and doesn’t believe that
the euro will fail, he said, according to the German newspaper.
Business is “still good,” the CEO told Sueddeutsche.  To contact the reporter on this story:
